docs.description: Poweliks is a trojan that does not require a file present on the victim's system. Instead, it relies on JavaScript embedded in the registry to store and launch itself. Once launched, the trojan checks for the presence of certain tools, such as PowerShell or .NET and may download them from a Microsoft server if they are not found. It also reaches out to its command and control server for further instructions and to download additional tools or malware. Poweliks first appeared in the summer of 2014.
